import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['home_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['home_score'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=11, color='green', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores across all matches?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_score'].plot(kind='hist', bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores across all matches?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Away Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_diff'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['score_diff'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['score_diff'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['score_diff'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the difference between home and away scores across all matches?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['division'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played by division?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played by date?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
